      /*

parameterised ML table of best model fit for subj vs. obj prob

11/01/2013 Markus Schaffner

*/

clear all
set more off

cd /Users/mas/Dropbox/OET
use "oetaug2010_pitstoplevel_v8.dta", clear

sort subjectid pitstopid

gen pse = psexpectation / 1000
gen female = 0
replace female = 1 if gender == 1

gen age2 = age*age

replace winpc = 2^-100 if winpc == 0
sum winpc


// clean up relevant var names
label var winpc "Objectiv prob."
label var pse "Subjective prob."

label var female "Gender (female=1)"
label var age "Age"
label var age2 "Age$^2$"

label var pitstopnum "Pitstop"

// malay seams a bit arbetrary
label var internationalstudent "International Student"


// there are 3 other catogories to weekly income (2 lower, 1 higher)
label var weekinc_2 "Weekly Income Average"

label var wealth_1 "Wealth Level Average"
label var wealth_2 "Wealth Level Poor"

// savouring
label var SBI_reminisce "SBI Reminisce"
label var SBI_anticipate "SBI Antacipate"
label var SBI_moment  "SBI Moment"

// arbritary selection of opt04 and opt 06
label var opt04 "Optimism: Disapp."
label var opt06 "Optimism: Low Exp."


label var lefthand "Lefthanded"
label var smoke "Smoking"
label var englishspeaker "Englishspeaker"

label var self_esteem_composite "Self Esteem"
label var medication "Medication"
label var depression "Depression"
label var alcohol_dummy "Alcohol"
label var happy "Happiness"
label var luckyans "Lucky Charm"
label var bettingjust "Betting is justified"
label var vegi "Vegetarian"
label var risk "Risk-aversion (HL)"

// education and parent qual seems doggy
label var mum_school "Mum Schooled"
label var dad_school "Dad Schooled"
label var dad_qual "Dad Qualified"
label var dad_hiqual "Dad Qual. Level"

// control
label var experiment "Experiment experience"
label var perfuni "Performance at Uni"


label var bet "Amount wagered"
label var failrate "Fail rate of the car"
label var winvalue  "Amount to be won"
label var sdwin "SD of win"
label var earnings "Real-Effort Earnings"
label var totalprpayout "Guess the winner"


label var shistakes "High Treatment"
label var slostakes "Low Treatment"
label var swealth "Wealth Treatment"


// data clean
// drop subjects with incomplete information
drop if subjectid == 505 | subjectid == 822 | subjectid == 653

// drop due to luckyans
drop if subjectid == 263 | subjectid == 714 | subjectid == 729

// replace risk as 5 for inconsistent (5 beeing the uniform random outcome, N=19)
replace risk = 5 if mi(risk)

// replace BMI with average (affects 404 and 723)
replace BMI = 22 if mi(BMI)

do oet_first_paper/do/varsets.do

sum $minimal


save oet_Oct2013.dta, replace
